# SEO Requirements

## Page Metadata

Every page must export `generateMetadata()` with:
- `title`, `description`, canonical URL
- OpenGraph (`og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`)

```typescript
// app/(pages)/about/page.tsx
import { aboutPageData } from "@/lib/data/pages/about";

export function generateMetadata(): Metadata {
  const { seo } = aboutPageData;
  return {
    title: seo.metaTitle,
    description: seo.metaDescription,
    openGraph: { title: seo.metaTitle, description: seo.metaDescription, images: seo.ogImageUrl ? [seo.ogImageUrl] : [] },
    alternates: { canonical: `/${seo.slug}` },
  };
}
```

## JSON-LD Structured Data

- Create reusable helpers in `lib/seo/jsonld.ts`
- Use schema.org types: `Organization`, `WebPage`, `FAQPage`, `BreadcrumbList`
- Include JSON-LD on all pages

## Sitemap & Robots

- Dynamic sitemap at `app/sitemap.ts`
- Robots config at `app/robots.ts`

## Never Skip

- Never create a page without `generateMetadata()`
- Never skip canonical URLs or OpenGraph data
